You can use this cloud function to manage user authentication. Here is the sample code for testing this cloud function in a mini program:

```js
// User Registration
wx.cloud.callFunction({
  name: 'custom-auth',
  data: {
    action: 'register',
    data: {
      username: 'test@example.com',
      password: 'password123'
    }
  }
}).then(res => {
  console.log('Registration result:', res)
})

// Response Example
{
  "userId": "user1"
}

// User Login
